  <data name="SensorStabilization_Generic" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Smart Sensors require a stabilization period of 5 minutes when first powered on before use. During stabilization, Snap Shot log is disabled and Trend Log storage is deferred. When sensors are fully stabilized, the sensor icon will disappear, the readings color will be black, and all log functions will be restored.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SensorStabilization_PID" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The PID sensor requires a MINIMUM of 15 minutes stabilization if the sensor has been used recently, and 30 minutes if the sensor is used on a frequent basis.  A 24-hour stabilization period is recommended if the sensor has been stored for a significant amount of time, exposed to high humidity or sources of contamination, or prior to user-calibration. Please refer to Sensor Tips and PID Guides for more information.</value>
